    {
      "key": "be13a57e-6ace-4455-8fc6-75e1ac4adcb6",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "*Check For Understanding Question(s) and solutions can be found in each lesson on Code Studio. These questions can be used for an exit ticket.*",
        "name": "Assessment: Check for Understanding",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "be13a57e-6ace-4455-8fc6-75e1ac4adcb6",
        "lesson_activity.key": "9ae441b3-5f8c-4fa0-9066-72e8393e5809"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "11717468-1347-4f1b-a878-8bf9448d8472",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have previously discussed examples of image filters that you have seen, and you have used your software engineering skills to create image filters. Let's look at some examples of how images are manipulated.",
        "name": "Is This Real?",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "11717468-1347-4f1b-a878-8bf9448d8472",
        "lesson_activity.key": "546ec862-bb53-4eae-8725-79692de81b81"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fd9b7564-cb4a-48c3-a8ee-34be3f9dc9cc",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the instructions for the Am I Real? activity.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "This activity can also be done without physical movement for different classroom setups. You could ask students to use a signal (raise left or right hand) to decide whether each person is real."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fd9b7564-cb4a-48c3-a8ee-34be3f9dc9cc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "546ec862-bb53-4eae-8725-79692de81b81"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "4e5a89a0-edc6-4479-a26f-99b18a1d730c",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show the first pair of images and have students choose which image they think is real.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Why did you choose your image as real? Why does the other image look less real?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share their reasoning for their choices, which may include features of an image that they believe is fake or real.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show which image is real and which is not real.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Show the second pair of images and have students choose which image they think is real.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Why did you choose your image as real? Why does the other image look less real?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share their reasoning for their choices, which may include features of an image that they believe is fake or real.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show which image is real and which is not real."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "4e5a89a0-edc6-4479-a26f-99b18a1d730c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "546ec862-bb53-4eae-8725-79692de81b81"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d3f88d2a-47eb-40cc-a3c0-454b44ee1f37",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Deep Fakes"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d3f88d2a-47eb-40cc-a3c0-454b44ee1f37",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7cc33670-7bcb-45fc-840c-bee67eabcebc",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "In each pair of images, one of them was a manipulated image called a deep fake.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7cc33670-7bcb-45fc-840c-bee67eabcebc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5b55d295-cef9-4c2e-8e66-2a3bd79c2853",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Where have you seen deep fakes before?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share examples of deep fakes they have seen, including in media and TV shows or on social media.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5b55d295-cef9-4c2e-8e66-2a3bd79c2853",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "d9309e1f-9746-48d5-8cb1-6d88cf89d47d",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *This is Not Morgan Freeman*.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What did this example make you wonder or feel?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share their thoughts and feelings about this example of deep fakes.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What do you think are some benefits of deep fakes?*\n* *What do you think are some harmful impacts of deep fakes?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students identify some benefits of deep fakes, such as automatically generating extras in movies. Students also identify some harmful impacts, like creating images and videos that look like someone communicating a message they may not actually support.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Retrieve-Pair-Share strategy to facilitate this discussion by directing students to write down their thoughts and ideas first, then pair up students to compare their answers and expand their notes. This allows time for individual processing and idea generation before sharing thoughts with others. Ask students to share the ideas they discussed with their partners as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "d9309e1f-9746-48d5-8cb1-6d88cf89d47d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "95deff99-88ec-419c-a885-7567e2e65e5a",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "To generate deep fakes, software engineers use a technique called machine learning. Machine learning, or ML, uses data and models to make predictions and decisions. This requires lots of data to improve the accuracy of the predictions and decisions. For deep fakes, this requires lots of images for the program to learn from.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "95deff99-88ec-419c-a885-7567e2e65e5a",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "18c97ff9-d7db-4e04-a2e7-fbe0d864047e",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Given the harmful impacts of deep fakes, should software engineers continue to develop them? Why or why not?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share their ideas about whether or not software to create deep fakes should be developed. Students justify their ideas with positive or negative impacts of deep fakes.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ask students to consider their role as software engineers in creating software that enables people to create deep fakes. If students support the technology, have students consider if they would implement restrictions or limitations in creating deep fakes."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "18c97ff9-d7db-4e04-a2e7-fbe0d864047e",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e5ce85cc-2859-4432-82cd-a6ff0049fa42",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "While some use image manipulation techniques to create deep fakes, these techniques are also used to identify objects and faces.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Object Detection",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e5ce85cc-2859-4432-82cd-a6ff0049fa42",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "db3f9a19-4ee8-44e2-961c-1473ca45dc31",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "**Do This:** Show the examples of edge detection:\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Detect abnormalities, such as tumors, in the body\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Detect curves in fingertips for fingerprint recognition\n* <i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> Detect other vehicles and people on the road\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio complete Levels 1, 2, and 3. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Image Manipulations"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "db3f9a19-4ee8-44e2-961c-1473ca45dc31",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5b6dba4e-f47b-4b1a-a7e4-af70f442d516",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5b6dba4e-f47b-4b1a-a7e4-af70f442d516",
        "lesson_activity.key": "1265269e-200d-482a-b171-8b30e720151d"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c2974b65-ae81-43a8-a866-7153a015aefd",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
