    {
      "key": "525d341d-88c8-46b8-b19d-7c445479092f",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "You did some brainstorming for your Creative Coding Project in a previous lesson. Let's now take some time to create an initial plan to guide your development processes in upcoming lessons. Your planning might include outlines, rough drafts, flowcharts, UML diagrams, or pseudocode for key algorithms in your program. Take a look at your Project Planning Board to decide what task you need to tackle first.",
        "name": "Planning Program Structure",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "525d341d-88c8-46b8-b19d-7c445479092f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a1ae577a-55d9-42b4-8239-7e4d5c5f13a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "f57cd2a8-5ee9-43fb-bb30-3c554163addc",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the first benchmark.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students work on their Creative Coding with The Theater Project.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Students might be unsure what task they should complete next. Encourage students to focus on brainstorming and planning tasks to identify the personal interest or problem they want to portray or address in their program and identify the major components that they need to develop. Refer students to pages six through eleven for planning space and templates."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "f57cd2a8-5ee9-43fb-bb30-3c554163addc",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a1ae577a-55d9-42b4-8239-7e4d5c5f13a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "83c2a2a8-6205-4e95-9e68-05436c0d70f1",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students update their Project Planning Board and Project Backlog with any tasks they completed, changed, or added."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "83c2a2a8-6205-4e95-9e68-05436c0d70f1",
        "lesson_activity.key": "a1ae577a-55d9-42b4-8239-7e4d5c5f13a4"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "a65024a0-78c7-4ac3-92dd-fa8b051b9f5c",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "10",
        "name": "The private Keyword"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "a65024a0-78c7-4ac3-92dd-fa8b051b9f5c",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "667a201e-91d4-441c-88e2-8a6b75c0bd06",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have used access modifiers like `private` to implement data encapsulation so other classes cannot directly modify the values stored in instance variables. We have also used `public` with constructors and methods so other classes can create instances of a class and use its methods. The `private` access modifier can be used to prevent access to methods from outside a class.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "667a201e-91d4-441c-88e2-8a6b75c0bd06",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "aad1475c-b8d1-41ec-af4e-617ecd9fa1f2",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio complete Levels 1, 2, and 3. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: Private Methods"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "aad1475c-b8d1-41ec-af4e-617ecd9fa1f2",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fe29cb50-0464-4f8b-9f9c-cc4d8ed331ba",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fe29cb50-0464-4f8b-9f9c-cc4d8ed331ba",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6a0d3054-3039-494d-a7df-ec30841fd5e9",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Like `private` instance variables, `private` methods cannot be accessed from outside of the class. Let's take a closer look at how this works.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Private Methods",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6a0d3054-3039-494d-a7df-ec30841fd5e9",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "361ce27a-b065-4939-9ff7-d78dc7995c03",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Show the video – *Private Methods*.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Videos are used throughout the curriculum to spark discussions, supplement key concepts with additional explanations and examples, and expose students to the various roles and backgrounds of individuals in computer science.\n\nWhile interacting with the video, turn on closed captioning so students can also read along as they watch.\n\nTo encourage active engagement and reflection, use one or more of the strategies discussed in the [**Guide to Curriculum Videos**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1FqIUpJg6MrgdtbFGLobSojOz0u1m5Jge1nMAjUqI5ZM/edit?usp=sharing)."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "361ce27a-b065-4939-9ff7-d78dc7995c03",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5176ce8f-21bc-4729-acc3-2d8daf8e9554",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to demonstrate the functionality of a `private` method.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *Why would we want to use a `private` method?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest using a `private` method as a helper method to perform a task within the class. Students identify that a `private` method can help keep a `public` method easy to read and maintain since specific tasks can be decomposed into `private` and `public` methods.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Ask additional guiding questions to help students make this connection. For example:\n* *Let's say the Joyful Pastries Food Truck business wants to automatically apply a discount to all orders that have more than six desserts. How could a private method be used in this scenario?*"
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5176ce8f-21bc-4729-acc3-2d8daf8e9554",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "c502ee2b-bfbf-48dc-aa5d-daa4d9ae7297",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 4 on Code Studio to complete Levels 4, 5, and 6. Students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to complete choice levels on Levels 5 and 6 to practice writing `private` methods.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: Private Methods",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding is an AP-style multiple choice question that can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of calling `private` methods.\n\nThe practice levels can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of writing and calling `private` methods."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "c502ee2b-bfbf-48dc-aa5d-daa4d9ae7297",
        "lesson_activity.key": "7fb08d0d-c4bd-4b70-9a49-a9feb8af54c8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "3ffdb13f-3a7e-43e2-9342-a0f5d8d5c5ff",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We just learned a lot of new information today, which may have even answered some of the Need to Know questions you wrote down about the Creative Coding Project. As we progress through the unit, it is helpful to stop and note what we have learned that is related to or useful for the project.",
        "name": "Revisiting the Need to Knows",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "3ffdb13f-3a7e-43e2-9342-a0f5d8d5c5ff",
        "lesson_activity.key": "83a56575-2a7f-4124-9b63-6bbe66989aa8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "88b8b967-c660-4cf3-a28f-84d5cfd74a15",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students review the questions they wrote in the \"Need to Know\" column on page two of their Creative Coding with The Theater Project Planning Guide. Students add new questions to this column, check off any answered questions, and write the answers to any questions in the \"Learned\" column.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they added to their chart with a partner.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, you can also have students share as a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "88b8b967-c660-4cf3-a28f-84d5cfd74a15",
        "lesson_activity.key": "83a56575-2a7f-4124-9b63-6bbe66989aa8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8625caaa-5bf1-4b3a-8f90-0c10dc0482f8",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 7 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8625caaa-5bf1-4b3a-8f90-0c10dc0482f8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "83a56575-2a7f-4124-9b63-6bbe66989aa8"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5906fa3e-aa98-4bf6-bd43-0bf60463ce44",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5906fa3e-aa98-4bf6-bd43-0bf60463ce44",
