    {
      "key": "22d883d8-72fd-407f-a2a7-1d4eb7cc085f",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "*Check For Understanding Question(s) and solutions can be found in each lesson on Code Studio. These questions can be used for an exit ticket.*",
        "name": "Assessment: Check for Understanding",
        "progression_name": "Check for Understanding"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "22d883d8-72fd-407f-a2a7-1d4eb7cc085f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "c15ca18c-ccc3-414b-b801-9363c3f7b2f9"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "37e20cbd-adb6-4475-a6cc-4d9201fae9b8",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned a lot about constructors and parameters so far and how we can use these to instantiate objects with default values or specific values. Today, we will learn more about how parameters function in Java and explore ways we can minimize redundancies in our code.",
        "name": "Anticipation Guide",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "37e20cbd-adb6-4475-a6cc-4d9201fae9b8",
        "lesson_activity.key": "eddeb11b-4da8-4570-bb22-aafa9beae590"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "6650d061-a62e-4845-8735-ef4a7c66b6fe",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Distribute:** Give each student a copy of the Anticipation Guide handout.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to respond to the prompts in the Before column on the Anticipation Guide. Have students compare their responses with a neighbor.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Emphasize to students that the goal is to make a guess for each statement based on what they know about Java so far rather than to determine the correct answer. These are concepts students should look out for throughout the lesson, and they will revisit the Anticipation Guide at the end of the lesson to review and revise their responses."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "6650d061-a62e-4845-8735-ef4a7c66b6fe",
        "lesson_activity.key": "eddeb11b-4da8-4570-bb22-aafa9beae590"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "e50166d5-e431-4171-9054-95fd5fe1b1b7",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the lesson objectives.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the Question of the Day.",
        "duration": "5",
        "name": "Introduction"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "e50166d5-e431-4171-9054-95fd5fe1b1b7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "140a4840-3775-44e1-8d8b-cdf51eacee7f",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We previously learned that parameters are local variables. These variables exist only within the block of code in which they are declared. Let's take a closer look at how these parameters are used in Java.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "140a4840-3775-44e1-8d8b-cdf51eacee7f",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "330a4bc0-f897-4b45-8e1b-9aa7c6370991",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 1 on Code Studio to predict the program's outcome, then run the program to compare their predictions to the actual outcome.",
        "progression_name": "Predict and Run: Constructors and Scope"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "330a4bc0-f897-4b45-8e1b-9aa7c6370991",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "dd139234-9706-4e54-ba5d-ea34d96ed9ff",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** Click through the animated slide to display the prompts.\n* *What did you notice about the code in this program?*\n* *What do you wonder about the code in this program?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students notice that the instance variables are assigned default values based on their data types instead of the values specified in the constructor call. They also notice that the parameter names are the same as the instance variables. Students may wonder why the instance variables were assigned default values or how Java knows which variable to use when the names are the same."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "dd139234-9706-4e54-ba5d-ea34d96ed9ff",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "aa8408b0-d471-4aa2-b01c-6b0d5e012b40",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Recall that the formal parameters are local variables and explain that these are referenced first instead of the instance variables.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 2 on Code Studio to complete Levels 2, 3, and 4. Students investigate the program, make changes to the program as prompted, and observe the results.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "The this Keyword",
        "progression_name": "Investigate and Modify: The this Keyword"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "aa8408b0-d471-4aa2-b01c-6b0d5e012b40",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "8dced127-d556-452c-bbcc-9e477deba7b7",
      "position": 6,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Have students share what they discovered from the modifications they made to the code.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *What does the word \"scope\" mean to you?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students share definitions of scope, such as how much of a topic or area is being covered or investigating something.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Use the Hold That Thought strategy to allow students to write down their thoughts on paper first. Emphasize that they do not need to write complete sentences – they can write a few words, bullet points, draw a quick sketch, or anything else that will help them gather and recall their thoughts when it is time to share with the class.\n\nHave students share examples of where they have heard or used the word \"scope\" before. Prompt students to consider how these definitions and examples might be related to its use in programming."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "8dced127-d556-452c-bbcc-9e477deba7b7",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "760d2ee2-e637-4f77-870a-5c20568c7c24",
      "position": 7,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Click through the animated slide to define and explain ***scope***.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Introduce the `this` keyword and explain its functionality.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Discuss:** *How does using the `this` keyword make our code more efficient and minimize redundancies?*\n\n**Discussion Goal:** Students suggest that using the same names for the parameters as the instance variables makes it easier to identify the purpose of the parameters and associate them to the instance variables. Students also note that using the `this` keyword to call a different constructor in the class makes it easier to reuse existing code instead of rewriting the code to assign the values to the instance variables."
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "760d2ee2-e637-4f77-870a-5c20568c7c24",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "2069172b-bee9-4491-b83f-a6fbec6d0df4",
      "position": 8,
      "properties": {
        "description": "We have learned a lot about writing constructors that we can use to instantiate objects in our programs! Let's practice putting what we have learned so far together to write constructors in our classes.",
        "duration": "15",
        "name": "Putting It All Together",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "2069172b-bee9-4491-b83f-a6fbec6d0df4",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "17e6e22e-f29c-4379-b5f0-5cd60c5d234d",
      "position": 9,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students to Level 5 on Code Studio to complete Levels 5, 6, and 7. On Level 5, students complete a Check for Understanding, then continue to Level 6 to practice writing no-argument and parameterized constructors in a class. On Level 7, students write parameterized constructors in the `Dessert` class.",
        "progression_name": "Practice: The this Keyword",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "assessmentOpportunity",
            "markdown": "The Check for Understanding and practice level can be used as a formative assessment to gauge understanding of the key terms and using the this keyword with parameterized constructors in a class."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "17e6e22e-f29c-4379-b5f0-5cd60c5d234d",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "044659d3-ccf3-4520-91c1-927c1b168747",
      "position": 10,
      "properties": {
        "description": "This is a good time to commit our code and save our `Dessert` class to the Backpack. We will be adding to the classes throughout the unit as we learn more about designing classes and their components.",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "044659d3-ccf3-4520-91c1-927c1b168747",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "99338af1-04c6-4df4-8db7-ad62c68c3a56",
      "position": 11,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Play the music clip to cue committing their code and saving their `Dessert` class to the Backpack.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "Using music to cue transitions helps create routines in the classroom. When students hear cues, they know it is time to transition to a specific activity. Emphasize to students what the music clip means, and be consistent with the use of the music clip to cue the activity.\n\nClick the blue play icon on the slide to play the music cue."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "99338af1-04c6-4df4-8db7-ad62c68c3a56",
        "lesson_activity.key": "ad3bfa14-5bec-4448-9492-febd22b57ea5"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "fa1d9806-9750-429d-ad84-32eb0781fbe0",
      "position": 1,
      "properties": {
        "description": "Now that we have learned more about how parameters function in Java and explored ways to minimize redundancies in our code, let's revisit our Anticipation Guide from the beginning of the lesson.",
        "name": "Revisiting the Anticipation Guide",
        "remarks": true
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "fa1d9806-9750-429d-ad84-32eb0781fbe0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "56058967-2c1a-44ff-a2b6-980758055f25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "96cfc16e-c8a0-46dd-8d54-8ad23eae2e64",
      "position": 2,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Direct students respond to the prompts in the After column on the Anticipation Guide. Have students compare their responses with a neighbor.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "If time permits, have students share their Before and After responses as a class to recap what they learned."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "96cfc16e-c8a0-46dd-8d54-8ad23eae2e64",
        "lesson_activity.key": "56058967-2c1a-44ff-a2b6-980758055f25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "5c1a20ea-d65d-4125-85fc-b098b908e2b0",
      "position": 3,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the concepts covered in this lesson.\n\n<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Do This:** Review the Question of the Day.",
        "tips": [
          {
            "type": "teachingTip",
            "markdown": "The Unit 2 Guide includes the Question of the Day and an end-of-lesson reflection prompt for students to summarize what they have learned and reflect on their progress. Have students respond to these prompts after reviewing the concepts covered in this lesson to help them process and make meaningful connections with the new content."
          }
        ]
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "5c1a20ea-d65d-4125-85fc-b098b908e2b0",
        "lesson_activity.key": "56058967-2c1a-44ff-a2b6-980758055f25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "7615ba14-0c3c-4487-b66e-bb8be2affc99",
      "position": 4,
      "properties": {
        "description": "<i class=\"fa fa-list-alt\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></i> **Display:** Key Vocabulary"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "7615ba14-0c3c-4487-b66e-bb8be2affc99",
        "lesson_activity.key": "56058967-2c1a-44ff-a2b6-980758055f25"
      }
    },
    {
      "key": "321f7dfc-f832-4b88-b28b-661a170994cf",
      "position": 5,
      "properties": {
        "description": "---"
      },
      "seeding_key": {
        "activity_section.key": "321f7dfc-f832-4b88-b28b-661a170994cf",
